The paper deals with the problem of recovering sparse signals from linear measurements, which is a fundamental problem in signal processing and information theory. The use of prior distribution information of the sparse signal is a common theme in many sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
